{
  "name": "Door Traps (d20)",
  "_id": "zzbNpr3Xgj345Vsw",
  "img": "icons/svg/trap.svg",
  "description": "<p>Roll when a dungeon door is found to be <strong>trapped</strong>. Each result lists the effect and a way to circumvent it. Listen, search, and open suspect doors from the side with a 10-ft pole where possible; Find/Remove Traps disarms a found trap. Adjust dice and saves to your system.</p>",
  "results": [
    {
      "_id": "98yeWuNDPrUSK3Ys",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "<strong>Poisoned needle.</strong> A needle in the lock or handle pricks the opener — save vs. poison or suffer its effect (DM's poison: damage, sleep, or weakness). <em>Circumvent:</em> Spike/jam the lock; open with tools or a gloved hand, never bare skin; Remove Traps.",
      "img": "icons/svg/trap.svg",
      "weight": 1,
      "range": [
        1,
        1
